MARTINETES AND GALLINETAS.

There are other birds also, thought to be of the partridge kind, which are larger than a common hen, adorned with a variety of co- lours, and a beautiful erest, and of an agree- able savour.

DIFFERENT KINDS OF PHEASANTS.

Birds are found in Paraguay which, in some respects, resemble· European pheasants. The commonest species is the yacu. This bird is equal in size to asull grown hen ; its feathers are of a very black colour, and its flesh extremely well tasted. It mostly frequents woods near a river or lake.
